19 assistance of the Secretary, shall utilize their authorities in furtherance of the purposes of
20 this subtitle by carrying out programs for the conservation of endangered species and
21 threatened species listed pursuant to [§ 10–2A–04(f)] § 10–2A–04(G) of this subtitle, and
22 by taking any action necessary to insure that actions authorized, funded, or carried out by
23 them do not jeopardize the continued existence of the endangered species or threatened
24 species or result in the destruction or modification of habitat of the species which is deemed
25 by the Secretary to be critical.
26 (d) The Secretary shall adopt regulations necessary to implement this section.
27 SECTION 2. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That if the U.S. Fish and Wildlife
28 Service removes the black vulture from the list of protected species under the federal
29 Migratory Bird Treaty Act, or if the federal Migratory Bird Treaty Act is repealed, the
30 Department of Natural Resources shall promulgate regulations authorizing the taking of
31 black vultures in a similar manner and with the same authorizations as a Depredation
32 Permit issued by the U.S. Fish and Wildlife Service.
33 SECTION 2. 3. AND BE IT FURTHER ENACTED, That this Act shall take effect
34 October 1, 2026.

